@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About — World Cup 2026 Modeler</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>About World Cup 2026 Modeler</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This is an app for simulating the FIFA World Cup 2026 tournament from group stage to final.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="home-cards">
    <section class="home-card">
        <h2>What this app does</h2>
        <p>
            Enter group-stage scores or manually reorder teams, then choose winners in every knockout match and watch the full bracket update automatically.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-card">
        <h2>How data is stored</h2>
        <p>
            Your model is saved locally in your browser using <code>localStorage</code>. There is no backend service and no sign-in required.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-card">
        <h2>Ranking and bracket rules</h2>
        <p>
            Group standings use points, then goal difference, then goals for. The best eight third-placed teams are assigned to Round-of-32 slots with a deterministic rule that avoids same-group rematches.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section class="home-card">
        <h2>Project</h2>
        <p>
            World Cup 2026 Modeler is open source and published as a static site on GitHub Pages.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-card">
        <h2>Creator</h2>
        <p>
            Built by Johannes Ebner.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/Structed" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub: @@Structed</a><br />
            <a href="https://github.com/Structed/worldcup-modeler" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source repository</a>
        </p>
    </section>
</div>

<p class="footnote">
    Tip: use the Reset everything button on the Home page whenever you want to clear your current simulation and start over.
</p>
